<br><table border=2 class=menu width="100%"><td nowrap class=menuhead width=100%>
<a href="#" onclick="toggleView('notab', 'main206', 2);return false;" title="Click to Expand">Zone Translocates            Found!</a> &raquo;
</td><td class=menuhead nowrap>April 20th, 2001</td></tr><tr><td class=menudata colspan=2>
<div id="main206" style="display:none;">
<br><ul>           Heh.. that got your attention, aye? These spells have not been found.            They are not on vendors and they are not dropping from mobs. They are            in the spell data for the live servers and all this means is that if            someone was to find one, it could be cast. Why are they not found on            the live servers? Reason has it that the spells are still being modified            with a 'verification box' over on the Test Server. This will work much            like the pop-up you get when a cleric cast Resurrection on your corpse.          <p> If these new Translocates are finally found on mobs, do all of your            wizard brothers and sisters a favor... <u>do not</u> pay some ridiculous            price for them. Remember, these spells benefit the melee classes.. not            you.</p>         <br><br><i>To keep tabs on the status of these spells, keep an            eye on the Forums. If I learn anything on them, I will post to the news.</i><br><br>-Graffe</ul></div>
</td></tr></table>
