<br><table border=2 class=menu width="100%"><td nowrap class=menuhead width=100%>
<a href="#" onclick="toggleView('notab', 'main209', 2);return false;" title="Click to Expand">Spell Additions            and Changes</a> &raquo;
</td><td class=menuhead nowrap>April 17th, 2001</td></tr><tr><td class=menudata colspan=2>
<div id="main209" style="display:none;">
<br><ul>           We've got four new spells and one changed spell. Verant has added 'Zone            Translocate' spells to the world. These will allow wizards to target            a group member and send them to one of four zones. Here is the listing            of the Translocate spells -</p>         <blockquote>            <p><b>Translocate: Fay</b> (level 39, 225 mana) - sends targeted, grouped              PC to the wizard spires in Greater Faydark.</p>           <p><b>Translocate: Tox</b> (level 39, 225 mana) - sends targeted, grouped              PC to the wizard spires in Toxxulia Forest.</p>           <p><b>Translocate: North</b> (level 39, 225 mana) - sends targeted,              grouped PC to the wizard spires in North Karana.</p>           <p><b>Translocate: Combine</b> (level 39, 225 mana) - sends targeted,              grouped PC to the wizard spires in The Dreadlands of Kunark.</p>         </blockquote>         <p>The spell that was changed is the level 51 AE snare, Atol's Spectral            Shackles. The resistance check vs. magic was changed from +25 to +15.            This should allow us to snare the mobs with less resistances.</p>         <br><br>-Graffe</ul></div>
</td></tr></table>
<br><table border=2 class=menu width="100%"><td nowrap class=menuhead width=100%>
<a href="#" onclick="toggleView('notab', 'main210', 2);return false;" title="Click to Expand">Patch Day</a> &raquo;
</td><td class=menuhead nowrap>April 17th, 2001</td></tr><tr><td class=menudata colspan=2>
<div id="main210" style="display:none;">
<br><ul>           The patch is in and the servers are still down. Lots of changes and            additions in this patch. I highly reccomend reading through the <a href="patch041701.htm">full            patch message</a> to see what has changed. Here is a list of things            that directly effects us wizards -</p>         <ul>           <li>The marauding Tar Goos will no longer be assisted by the Geonids.              This should make at least one quest more available.</li>           <li>We have increased the spawn rate of Venril Sathir and his skeletal              remains. Please note that only Rangers and Druids will be able to              trigger the spawn for the skeletal remains, and those remains will              only be dropping items for those epic quests. Hopefully these changes              will dramatically reduce the competition and resentment over this              spawn.</li>           <li>We have reduced resistances to some spell types on some NPCs in              Sky Shrine and the Tower of Frozen Shadow. This is the beginning of              our overview of the resistances of NPCs in Velious.</li>         </ul>         <p>Once again, the link to the full patch message can be found by clicking            <a href="patch041701.htm">here</a>. </p>         <br><br><i>VS Spawn increased! Woo hoo!</i><br><br>-Graffe</ul></div>
</td></tr></table>
<br><table border=2 class=menu width="100%"><td nowrap class=menuhead width=100%>
<a href="#" onclick="toggleView('notab', 'main211', 2);return false;" title="Click to Expand">Absor On Class            Balancing</a> &raquo;
</td><td class=menuhead nowrap>April 12th, 2001</td></tr><tr><td class=menudata colspan=2>
<div id="main211" style="display:none;">
<br><ul>           Absor posted to the Developers Corner / Class Talks forum concerning            the class changes and balancing that many of us are waiting upon -          <blockquote> &quot;We have been receiving a fair amount of mail regarding            the status of changes to classes based on the items brought up in the            class talk threads that I started a while ago. Right now I have little            new information for you, but let me spend a moment talking about this.<br>           The team has read and reviewed the lists that I put together. We've            had several informal discussions about them, and a few formal discussions            about specific items on those lists.            <p>So far you've seen a lot of changes based on your input. They have              been going into the game as they get finished and tested. Things that              didn't require a lot of in-depth investigation on our part, such as              changing the Bread Pants for Bards, increasing the drop rates for              many Kunark spells, fixing the Track Corpse spell and many others.</p>           <p>And even some of the more complicated issues have been looked into.              Things like giving Druids and Shaman the ability to act as secondary              healers, upgrading Mark of Karn (a very complicated spell to balance),              the aggro created by debuff spells (and, yes, the aggro created by              healing spells), and others that have required a lot of consideration              have been added or changed.</p>           <p><b>We've also started on some of the much more complicated issues,              such as Wizards and their ability to do damage against certain NPCs              with the Bane spells.</b></p>           <p>To finish the lists we'll have to make the time to have some long              and complicated meetings over issues that can't be changed without              rather a lot of effect on the game world. We have not had those meeting              yet. Recently we decided that we would put PvP issues to the forefront,              considering that lack of attention they have had over the life of              EverQuest.</p>           <p>I just wanted to let you know that we haven't forgotten the issues              that you brought to our attention.</p>           <p>Alan&quot;</p>         </blockquote>         <p>A link to the original post can be found <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000087.html" target="_blank">here</a>.            You cannot post to the forums anymore so I invite you to share your            thoughts on a thread that has already been started <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=2618.topic">here</a>            in the General Discussion forum.</p>         <br><br><i>Thanks for the heads up Khadgar!</i><br><br>-Graffe</ul></div>
</td></tr></table>
