<br><table border=2 class=menu width="100%"><td nowrap class=menuhead width=100%>
<a href="#" onclick="toggleView('notab', 'main214', 2);return false;" title="Click to Expand">Questions Answered            (uh.. sorta..)</a> &raquo;
</td><td class=menuhead nowrap>April 10th, 2001</td></tr><tr><td class=menudata colspan=2>
<div id="main214" style="display:none;">
<br><ul>           Jaqe Ragnarok of Druzzil Ro visited the Fan Faire and was able to ask            the Magic Panel a couple questions -          <blockquote> "Harvest Spell Icon color is turning active prematurely -            After you cast harvest and the icon greys out why does it revert back            to its colored state prematurily after you use a right clickable item            such as Jboots. This is a real pain for soloing wizards that depend            heavily on this spell to reduce downtime. This icon needs to stay greyed            out till it is actually ready to use again and not be affected by right            clickable items.            <p> <b>Answer - We will look into that</b>            <p> Temperate Flux Staff - The text mesages in chat for the staff's              effect is not always received properly. There seems to be a dead spot              for this staff where you do not get any effect messages back from              the mob. If you are way out of range you will receive a message stating              "you are out of range" that and if you keep reducing the distance              to the mob you will eventually come to the point where you sometimes              get no messages, if you close the distance even more you will then              start receiving messages stating that the mob is either uncomfortable              or the mob has resisted the lower element spell. This is not a big              deal if the mob is snared and chasing you but if it is not snared              and you want to try to debuff it before you try to snare it again,              can prove to be a little tricky. I wish the staff would either state              you are out of range or one of the other two messages " the mob is              uncomfortable" or the "the mob has resisted the lower element spell".              Even though elevation does make this worse it can happen in a totally              flat area.            <p> <b>Answer - We wil look into that</b>"          </blockquote>         <p></p>         <br><br><i>Thanks Jaqe!</i><br><br>-Graffe</ul></div>
</td></tr></table>
