<br><table border=2 class=menu width="100%"><td nowrap class=menuhead width=100%>
<a href="#" onclick="toggleView('notab', 'main217', 2);return false;" title="Click to Expand">Fennin Ro Wizard            Faire</a> &raquo;
</td><td class=menuhead nowrap>April 9th, 2001</td></tr><tr><td class=menudata colspan=2>
<div id="main217" style="display:none;">
<br><ul>           Dynamite Shortfuze of Fennin Ro sent in info about a Wizard Faire that            is going to be held on Fennin Ro later this month -<br>         </p>         <blockquote>            <p>Hail good wizards of Norrath!</p>           <p>I come before you today with news of <b>Fennin Ro's</b> first ever              Wizard Faire! In months past, I have hosted a Rune Trade on Fennin              Ro, and the time has come to expand upon this, with a huge faire...              for wizards!</p>           <p>I'm hoping that this can be held on the <b>28th of April</b>. I know,              it's very early to discuss this, and I don't even know myself if I              will be available, but I've been getting pressure to start announcing              it (especially from Omnip, who is possibly the Faire's biggest supporter).              Let me explain how it works...</p>           <p>Before, at the rune faires, wizards of all levels would come together.              We would discuss life and have fun (the Ol'Tujim's Fierce Brew helped              with that I'm sure), but most prominently, we would trade runes. If              you needed a rune, you would ask if anyone had it, and you would likely              receive it. Conversely, if you had a rune someone else needed, you              would offer it to them. Higher level wizards were on hand to assist              lower levels in the research of their spells, and fun was had by all.</p>           <p>No changes are being made to that. We're just expanding on it. This              month, we will have contests, games, duels, the rune trade, and above              all, fun!</p>           <p>I would like to offer prizes of cash and items for this event, but              as this is an independant project and not one of any guild with a              large support base, my income restricts this from being much good.              I can offer prizes just fine, they just won't be good in many respects.              So much so that prizes would probably have just as much impact if              they weren't present. However, if you have any donations of items              or cash that you would like to put forward to this, please contact              me in-game and let me know. I won't ask that you give it to me until              the event (since I can't guaruntee my presence just yet), but I would              like to know that these things are available so I can plan ahead with              them in mind. If you can't get to me in-game, please contact me at              <a href="mailto:fenninrunes@hotmail.com">fenninrunes@hotmail.com</a></p>         </blockquote>         <blockquote>            <p>Also, I am just one wizard, and in past trades, I have had JUST enough              alcohol to please the masses. So if you'd like to bring some of your              own brew for all to sample, please, I wholeheartedly encourage it!</p>           <p>We have a few games in mind, and Omnip has some that she won't tell              me about (she says it's a surprise and she'll post it on the boards              herself), but we can only get better with help. So, if you've got              an idea for a game, again, contact me with the procedure and rules              at <a href="mailto:fenninrunes@hotmail.com">fenninrunes@hotmail.com</a></p>           <p>I'm really looking forward to this month, I expect it's going to              be the best we've had yet! I hope to see you there!<br>           </p>         </blockquote>         <p>I noticed a thread on the General Forum started on this.. if you have            any questions, you can e-mail <a href="mailto:fenninrunes@hotmail.com">Dynamite</a>            or visit the thread <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=2557.topic">here</a>.</p>         <br><br>-Graffe</ul></div>
</td></tr></table>
